# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# B2B MARKETPLACE — ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES TEMPLATE
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values
# NEVER commit the .env file to version control
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# Application
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=4001
API_PORT=4001

# Database (Supabase PostgreSQL)
# Get from: Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Database → Connection String
# Use Session Pooler (port 6543) for local development
POSTGRES_URL=postgresql://postgres.YOUR_PROJECT_REF:YOUR_PASSWORD@aws-0-ap-southeast-1.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true&connection_limit=1
POSTGRES_USER=postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=your_database_password

# DIRECT_URL is REQUIRED for Prisma migrations (bypasses PgBouncer connection pooler)
# This must be set even in development. Use the direct PostgreSQL port (5432), NOT the pooler port (6543)
# Without this, `prisma migrate deploy` will fail with a timeout error
DIRECT_URL=postgresql://postgres:YOUR_PASSWORD@db.YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co:5432/postgres

# Redis (optional in development — comment out to disable)
# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
# For cloud Redis: use Upstash free tier → https://upstash.com

# Elasticsearch (optional in development)
ELASTICSEARCH_URL=http://localhost:9200

# Authentication
# Generate with: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_minimum_32_characters_here
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your_nextauth_secret_minimum_32_characters_here
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:4000

# Payment Gateway (Razorpay)
# Get from: https://dashboard.razorpay.com → Settings → API Keys
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_test_your_test_key_id_here
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=your_test_key_secret_here

# SMS Gateway (MSG91)
# Get from: https://msg91.com → API → Auth Key
MSG91_AUTHKEY=your_msg91_auth_key_here

# Application URLs
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:4000
BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:4001
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:4000
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4001
# Internal API URL for server-side rendering (use internal Docker/VPC address in production)
# Falls back to NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL if not set
INTERNAL_API_URL=http://localhost:4001

# File Uploads
FILE_UPLOAD_DIR=./uploads
MAX_FILE_SIZE=10485760

# Security
BCRYPT_SALT_ROUNDS=12

# Encryption (AES-256-GCM) — REQUIRED for PII fields (buyer contact, Aadhaar)
# Generate with: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
ENCRYPTION_KEY=your_64_char_hex_encryption_key_generate_with_command_above

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info

# Feature Flags
FEATURE_FLAGS_MODE=database

# Government APIs (Sandbox — for development)
# GSTN_SANDBOX_KEY=your_gstn_sandbox_key
# DGFT_API_KEY=your_dgft_api_key
# GSTN_API_URL=https://api.gstin.in/sandbox
# INCOME_TAX_API_URL=https://sandbox.incometax.gov.in
# UDYAM_API_URL=https://udyamregistration.gov.in/api

# AWS S3 (optional — for future file storage migration)
# AWS_REGION=ap-south-1
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_access_key
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_secret_key
# AWS_BUCKET_NAME=your_bucket_name

# Monitoring (optional)
# DATADOG_API_KEY=your_datadog_key
# SENTRY_DSN=your_sentry_dsn
